= Annex: AZDZ-Club External Person Agreement EN-US Translation

This agreement outlines the terms and conditions for external participants who join AZDZ-Club activities. By participating in club activities, the external person agrees to the following terms and conditions.

== 1. Media and Publicity Consent

1.1. The external person consents that photos taken during club activities may be used for the club’s social media, repositories, and promotional materials. These photos will be used and issued under the Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0 (CC-BY-ND 4.0) license. The external person may use photos and materials from club activities for personal blogs or professional profiles (e.g., LinkedIn), under applicable licenses. When doing so, they must indicate that the activity was conducted by AZDZ-Club and credit the organizer appropriately. The activity should not be misrepresented or misused in any manner.

== 2. Equipment Usage and Responsibility

2.1. The external person agrees that any equipment used during the club activity should be reported for any damages or defects before and after usage. The external person cannot take any club equipment outside of the venue indicated in the activity log unless explicitly stated. The activity log will be provided to them via email if requested. They will not pass on the equipment to any other individual or club member. If any equipment is borrowed, it must be returned according to the stated rules, and the external person is responsible for any damages that occur during the usage. All damages and defects must be reported immediately, and the external person may be financially responsible for repairs if deemed necessary. The external person will not be permitted to borrow any further equipment if these terms are violated twice.

== 3. Information and Code Licensing

3.1. Any information or materials shared with the external person during club activities will be used solely for the purpose of the activity, and the external person agrees to respect the confidentiality and ownership of the materials provided. Any code or content they acquire from the club will be issued under the license indicated in the respective repository. The external person agrees to abide by the terms of the repository’s license when using or contributing to the materials.

== 4. General Conduct and Compliance

4.1. The external person agrees to conduct themselves respectfully and professionally during all club activities. Any violations of the club’s guidelines may result in removal from the activities. The club reserves the right to modify activity rules and requirements as necessary to ensure the smooth running of all events and operations.

== 5. No Storage of Personal Information

5.1. Any personal information the external person shares with the club will be used solely for the purpose of the activities they are participating in. This information will not be stored beyond the recording of their attendance in the activity log and the documentation of this agreement.
